Here is what is available in each folder :

Deliverables : Deliverables Documentation
Presentation : Presentation PDF , Link to Canva PPT
data : All tables turned into final database (present in outputs folder) as knowledgebase, sourced from github.com/VinayakAKattimani/transaction_failure_analysis
local_embedding_model : Local Embedding model used in our project (MiniLM-L3-v2), do Read this folders README to complete the model.
modules : all .py files used during runtime
notebooks : all .ipynb files that were run once to get Final dataset, FAISS artifacts for knowledge base and also testing rag pipeline and evaluation.
outputs : Contains all FAISS Artifacts and our final database for knowledge base, an dataset exploring .ipynb file
phi2_gguf : supposed to have the LLM model phi-2.Q4_K_M.gguf, do Read this folders README to download the model.

After all steps are done, install everything in requirements.txt, just change a few paths suited to your local machine, run the app.py file in terminal with stremlit run app.py
